1
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:15,753
My bleeding feet!

2
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:17,792
Hello, Mrs. Joseph.

3
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:20,310
l like your hair.
ls that strawberry blonde?

4
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:22,158
You're only jealous.

5
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:25,076
What's for the old man's
supper tonight?

6
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:28,158
He'll be lucky to get
faggots and pease pudd, he will.

7
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:31,193
Well, he can't do much
on that, can he?

8
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:35,873
All l want him for
is to keep me feet warm.

9
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:37,912
Excuse me, dearie.

10
00:02:38,320 --> 00:02:39,116
Here, Gert.

11
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:43,393
l wouldn't mind having this little lot
in my stocking for Christmas.

12
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:46,638
What would you do with him?
You've been a widow too long.

13
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:48,199
You speak for yourself.

14
00:02:48,480 --> 00:02:51,870
lt's like riding a bicycle.
You never forget how.

15
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:55,313
l'll tell you what l'll do.

16
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:58,558
l'll send my Alfie to you.
He's not bad once he gets going.

17
00:02:59,160 --> 00:03:02,038
Well, l hope he's well-sprung.

18
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:47,670
Morning.

19
00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:51,038
Looking for someone, mate?

20
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:56,832
Nice day, isn't it?

21
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:37,870
Sorry.

22
00:04:49,520 --> 00:04:51,078
Hackman's in the staff room.

23
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:53,510
Where he bleeding well belongs.

24
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,150
Good morning.

25
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:18,149
My name is Thackeray.
l'm a new teacher.

26
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,319
We were expecting you.

27
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:24,832
So you're the new lamb
for the slaughter.

28
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,635
Or should l say...

29
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:28,069
...black sheep?

30
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,636
No, just a teacher, Mr. Hackman.

31
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:33,549
l'm not Hackman.
Perish the thought.

32
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:36,391
He's departed,
God rest his soul.

33
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:40,430
He's probably pouring out his woes
to the divisional officer by now.

34
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:42,269
Weston.

35
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:47,079
l'm Mrs. Evans, Grace.
Deputy head.

36
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:48,395
Mrs. Evans.

37
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:50,318
Have you seen any children yet?

38
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:53,398
l looked in on Mr. Hackman's class
for a moment.

39
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:56,391
l take them for domestic science.

40
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,069
Like a cup of tea?

41
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:01,555
No, thank you, not just now.

42
00:06:03,520 --> 00:06:04,953
You been teaching long?

43
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:07,237
This is my first appointment.

44
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:09,752
We call them jobs.

45
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:11,075
American, are you?

46
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:13,316
British, from British Guiana.

47
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:15,477
But l spent some years
in the States.

48
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:18,274
-Where?
-ln California.

49
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:20,472
Weather as good as they say?

50
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:22,034
lt's better.

51
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:27,230
What was your subject?

52
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:30,197
What did you major in?

53
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:32,038
Engineering.

54
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:37,309
l must be off.
Make yourself at home.

55
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:39,556
Wander around, if you like,
or stay here.

56
00:06:39,840 --> 00:06:41,637
l'll introduce you at lunch.

57
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:43,069
Thank you.

58
00:07:19,960 --> 00:07:22,428
This is Gillian, Mr. Thackeray.

59
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:24,714
Gillian Blanchard.

60
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:29,911
She's new here too.
Came the day before yesterday.

61
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:32,118
-Tea, Gillian?
-Thank you.

62
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,560
This is Mr. Mark Thackeray,
the new replacement.

63
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:40,876
Jose Dawes,
Euphemia Phillips.

64
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:42,832
They teach the little ones.

65
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,348
Theo Weston, you know.

66
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:47,234
l've had the pleasure.
He mistook me for Hackman.

67
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:49,238
-He's fled.
-l don't blame him.

68
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:51,351
That's enough to destroy anybody.

69
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:53,232
He got what he deserved.

70
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:54,988
l'm Clinty Clintridge.

71
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:56,759
Clinty's a marvelous artist.

72
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:59,634
Got one at the Royal Academy
a couple of years ago.

73
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:01,592
Teaching provides the bread and butter.

74
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:04,678
Well, that's all the staff
except for Mr. Bell...

75
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:06,473
...our P.T. instructor.

76
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:08,591
l hope you're
going to stay with us.

77
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:11,229
l shouldn't if l were you, old man.

78
00:08:11,520 --> 00:08:13,192
Row home while you can.

79
00:08:13,440 --> 00:08:15,112
Don't discourage him, Weston.

80
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:17,918
Well, l must go.

81
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:20,839
l have to fix a bath
for a girl in Clinty's class.

82
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:21,950
Why?

83
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:24,276
Kids complained again.
Won't sit near her.

84
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:25,549
What's the matter?

85
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:27,558
Personal hygiene problems.

86
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,478
Fourteen and helpless.

87
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:31,599
You men are lucky.

88
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:35,152
The things we women have to do
for these kids.

89
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,635
Gillian, dear...

90
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,513
...encourage him to stay.

91
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:47,634
Why is it everyone thinks
l need encouraging?

92
00:08:47,920 --> 00:08:49,638
They said the same to me.

93
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:54,153
There's something frightening but
also challenging about this school.

94
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:57,671
There's no form of corporal
punishment or any punishment.

95
00:08:57,960 --> 00:08:58,995
None?

96
00:08:59,280 --> 00:09:01,794
l have no real teaching experience.
l'm lost.

97
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:03,911
l don't have any experience either.

98
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:07,477
But it'll be much easier for you.

99
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:10,277
l'm a little afraid of them.

100
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:12,314
Midday dance session.

101
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:16,070
At lunch, the older kids use the hall.
l sometimes join them.

102
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:17,918
Even the old man shakes a leg.

103
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:20,668
Dancing is merely their way
of keeping fit...

104
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:24,316
...for the more exciting pastime
of teacher baiting.

105
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,636
Couldn't you be
a bit less discouraging?

106
00:09:26,920 --> 00:09:29,070
lt's the last thing l want to do.

107
00:09:30,280 --> 00:09:31,759
The music's louder than usual.

108
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:34,873
They're probably celebrating
victory over Hackman.

109
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:37,556
l better go and see Mr. Florian.

110
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:39,319
l'll show you the way.

111
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:15,795
-They're good, aren't they?
-l suppose so.

112
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:20,953
The head's study is this way.

113
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:28,155
Do you two....

114
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:32,435
Do you two shake?

115
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:36,954
Well, l'll see you later,
Mr. Thackeray.

116
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:38,355
Well?

117
00:10:43,520 --> 00:10:44,396
Thank you.

118
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:46,875
But l have to go
and see the principal.

119
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:06,630
You have excellent qualifications,
astonishing ones, in fact...

120
00:11:06,920 --> 00:11:08,672
...as a communications engineer.

121
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:11,554
Field experience in South America....

122
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:13,678
Why do you want to be a teacher?

123
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:14,950
Reasons.

124
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:17,629
You've already tried to get
an engineering post?

125
00:11:17,920 --> 00:11:20,036
l tried for 1 8 months, sir.

126
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:25,275
We have no blueprint in North Quay.

127
00:11:25,640 --> 00:11:28,996
Most of our children are
rejects from other schools.

128
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:31,475
We must help and teach them
as best we can...

129
00:11:31,760 --> 00:11:33,318
...and as much as we can.

130
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:36,319
The local authorities are not
totally on our side.

131
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:40,434
And if you accept this position,
you'll be entirely on your own.

132
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:43,917
l and the staff will do
everything we can to help you...

133
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:47,317
...but success or failure
will depend entirely upon you.

134
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:49,756
What's it to be?

135
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:51,348
l want the job, sir.

136
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:53,670
Good.

137
00:11:54,160 --> 00:11:55,149
Then it's settled.

138
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:56,668
Tomorrow, you'll take over
Hackman's class.

139
00:11:58,280 --> 00:11:59,315
Sapiano.

140
00:12:00,160 --> 00:12:01,149
Wong.

141
00:12:02,640 --> 00:12:03,675
Osgood.

142
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:05,470
Tuffen.

143
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:07,356
Pegg.

144
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:09,276
Pegg?

145
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:13,635
Joseph.

146
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:15,629
Dare.

147
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:19,156
Potter.

148
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:20,996
Potter.

149
00:12:21,880 --> 00:12:22,710
Denham.

150
00:12:25,960 --> 00:12:26,836
Buckley.

151
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:29,069
Purcell.

152
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:32,275
Fernman.

153
00:12:33,280 --> 00:12:34,190
Jackson.

154
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:36,834
Strong.

155
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:39,229
Seales.

156
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:44,836
-Palmer.
-Yes, Guvnor.

157
00:12:45,680 --> 00:12:46,749
Campbell.

158
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:47,836
Present.

159
00:12:50,760 --> 00:12:53,832
l don't know how much you know,
so we'll start from scratch.

160
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:55,798
First, as l call your name...

161
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:59,629
...will you read anything you like
from one of your schoolbooks?

162
00:13:01,520 --> 00:13:02,555
Fernman.

163
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:04,275
Right.

164
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:09,073
''Only those who...

165
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:11,958
...arrived on...

166
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:13,993
...horseback...

167
00:13:14,520 --> 00:13:18,195
-...or in a public coach.''
-Thank you.

168
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:20,510
Denham.

169
00:13:27,560 --> 00:13:30,870
'' lf 1 4 hens lay an egg
a day for 30 days...

170
00:13:31,160 --> 00:13:35,119
...how much are the eggs a dozen,
and how many have you to sell?''

171
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:36,956
Moira Joseph.

172
00:13:39,160 --> 00:13:42,630
'' Pete Gilroy's weight
and the ever-tightening noose...

173
00:13:42,920 --> 00:13:44,433
...about her neck...

174
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:49,390
...began slightly to impede
the wild mare's speed.

175
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:53,310
But Pete was only too fully aware
of what his fate would be...

176
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:55,670
...for he could not hope
to escape death...

177
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:58,110
...from being battered and crushed.''

178
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:02,871
Put that away, please.

179
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:12,510
Thank you.

180
00:14:26,560 --> 00:14:28,152
Would anyone else like to read?

181
00:14:30,560 --> 00:14:32,596
-Your name, please.
-Pamela Dare.

182
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,072
''And he had learned to love.

183
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:37,429
l know not why...

184
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:40,393
...for this in such as him
seemed strange of mood.

185
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:42,154
But thus it was.

186
00:14:42,560 --> 00:14:44,471
And though
in solitude's small part...

187
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:47,149
...the nipped affections
have to grow.

188
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:48,999
ln him this glowed...

189
00:14:49,280 --> 00:14:51,953
...when all beside
had ceased to glow.''

190
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:06,474
Thank you, Miss Dare.

191
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:08,876
Next, weights and measures.

192
00:15:09,560 --> 00:15:10,834
What's avoirdupois?

193
00:15:11,120 --> 00:15:12,917
-Avoir de what?
-Avoirdupois.

194
00:15:13,240 --> 00:15:14,355
Weights.

195
00:15:16,760 --> 00:15:19,069
Heavyweight, light-heavy,
cruiserweight...

196
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:21,920
...middle, light, bantam,
fly, featherweight.

197
00:15:22,280 --> 00:15:24,157
Thank you very much.

198
00:15:28,520 --> 00:15:31,193
lt's encouraging that
you have a sense of humour.

199
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:35,272
lt seems you know so little
and are easily amused...

200
00:15:35,560 --> 00:15:37,391
...l can look forward to a happy time.

201
00:15:39,880 --> 00:15:42,030
Copy down the following tables.

202
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:45,038
Who does he think he is, there?

203
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:46,514
The cheeky devil.

204
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,274
Hello, ducks.

205
00:16:08,960 --> 00:16:10,757
Thought you might need this.

206
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:12,228
How'd it go?

207
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:16,514
Let's just say, battle was joined.

208
00:16:21,760 --> 00:16:24,069
l don't know what we'd do
without a cuppa.

209
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:25,588
What's your name?

210
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:28,071
l know that.
l mean, your other name.

211
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:29,429
Mark.

212
00:16:30,680 --> 00:16:32,238
Couple of things, Mark.

213
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,991
We all know the old man's views.

214
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:37,316
Basically, we agree with them.

215
00:16:37,760 --> 00:16:39,830
But he's safe in an office.

216
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:43,916
These kids come from homes where
an order is accompanied by a blow.

217
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:47,317
One rude word to their parents,
the roof will hit them.

218
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:50,634
There's nothing like that
going on here, right?

219
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:54,797
So they've got us
at a great disadvantage.

220
00:16:57,520 --> 00:17:00,512
Hackman tried to be popular.
He hung himself.

221
00:17:01,400 --> 00:17:04,472
Weston couldn't care less
about them, and that's no good.

222
00:17:08,760 --> 00:17:10,830
l can't guide you...

223
00:17:12,360 --> 00:17:15,477
...but don't take any nonsense
from these little tykes.

224
00:17:16,840 --> 00:17:19,070
They're good kids, Mark,
most of them.

225
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:25,039
But if you don't solve them,
they'll break you and damn quickly.

226
00:17:25,320 --> 00:17:26,594
That's been tried...

227
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:27,949
...by experts.

228
00:17:29,360 --> 00:17:31,351
They're very expert.

229
00:17:32,080 --> 00:17:34,196
Please can l leave the room, Guv?

230
00:17:35,520 --> 00:17:37,795
Yes. And it's ''Thackeray.''

231
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:39,555
Yes, Guv.

232
00:17:46,680 --> 00:17:50,070
Most of you girls help your mothers
with the shopping.

233
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:53,353
So sorry, Mr. Thackeray.

234
00:17:53,760 --> 00:17:56,115
Proper drafty in these parts,
isn't it?

235
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:00,829
About multiplying...

236
00:18:01,840 --> 00:18:04,274
...there are a few
valuable tricks to know.

237
00:18:04,520 --> 00:18:08,718
Say that you're offered roast beef
at seven shillings per pound.

238
00:18:09,360 --> 00:18:10,270
Potter.

239
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:12,316
Must you do that?

240
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:15,035
l can't help it, Sir.
lt's me desk.

241
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:16,429
Poor old Potts!

242
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:35,150
Sit down.

243
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:49,033
l'll speak with the caretaker
about it after school.

244
00:18:49,280 --> 00:18:50,235
lsn't he nice?

245
00:18:53,760 --> 00:18:54,510
l hope l didn't miss nothing.

246
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:56,916
Where was we?
About shopping or some--?

247
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:59,031
That's enough, Denham.

248
00:18:59,320 --> 00:19:02,835
l was only asking, Mr. Thackeray.
l don't wanna miss nothing.

249
00:19:03,080 --> 00:19:07,039
Bert, he was just about to show us
a new and valuable trick.

250
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:10,750
-When you're shopping, you see--
-l said, that's enough.

251
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:12,470
Sit down.

252
00:19:23,040 --> 00:19:25,713
Do exercise four, five and six.

253
00:19:35,840 --> 00:19:37,398
Very quietly.

254
00:19:40,760 --> 00:19:44,070
Don't worry.
The worst is still to come.

255
00:19:44,320 --> 00:19:46,834
You're still getting
the silent treatment.

256
00:19:47,120 --> 00:19:48,792
What's the next phase?

257
00:19:49,480 --> 00:19:52,552
Well, unless you can work up
a little black magic...

258
00:19:53,120 --> 00:19:56,430
...these little bastards have
a multitude of tricks.

259
00:20:00,640 --> 00:20:02,358
Why did you take up teaching?

260
00:20:03,400 --> 00:20:05,709
lt's good to have some kind of a job.

261
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:12,312
But l'm teaching them nothing.
l'm not even getting to first base.

262
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:15,628
Don't worry,
your lot leaves this term.

263
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:17,154
The next will be better.

