00:57:08,120 --> 00:57:10,395
Don't spend too much time
alone with her.

771
00:57:12,200 --> 00:57:13,872
Why didn't you ask Gillian?

772
00:57:16,680 --> 00:57:19,353
l thought you'd be wiser.

773
00:57:23,400 --> 00:57:24,515
Thanks.

774
00:57:53,360 --> 00:57:56,033
Hello, Sir!
We can't have you queuing up.

775
00:57:56,480 --> 00:57:59,313
lt's Sir. He teaches
our Moira up at North Quay.

776
00:57:59,600 --> 00:58:02,034
He's only got an hour for his lunch.

777
00:58:02,320 --> 00:58:04,117
-What'll it be?
-Half a dozen oranges.

778
00:58:04,400 --> 00:58:06,231
You'll like them.
They're lovely.

779
00:58:06,520 --> 00:58:07,589
Here you are, Guv.

780
00:58:08,240 --> 00:58:10,800
Penny's wedding cake.
Jeannie's older sister.

781
00:58:11,080 --> 00:58:13,196
She got married,
so here's a bit of cake.

782
00:58:14,600 --> 00:58:16,192
Jeannie Clark.

783
00:58:16,680 --> 00:58:18,193
Yes, Miss Clark.

784
00:58:18,560 --> 00:58:21,711
That was a lovely museum outing.
Will they do it again?

785
00:58:23,560 --> 00:58:25,755
We're trying to arrange one a week.

786
00:58:26,040 --> 00:58:27,393
That'd be lovely, won't it?

787
00:58:28,000 --> 00:58:31,470
The more education, the better.
That's what l always say.

788
00:58:32,040 --> 00:58:34,873
lt's a proper bleeder,
what with the bomb and all.

789
00:58:35,160 --> 00:58:37,958
Ain't the bombs.
lt's them bleeding Yanks!

790
00:58:38,280 --> 00:58:40,999
Shut your gob!
My Gert's married to a Yank.

791
00:58:41,280 --> 00:58:43,510
And a proper nice gent he is and all.

792
00:58:43,800 --> 00:58:45,677
Keep your opinions to yourself!

793
00:58:45,960 --> 00:58:49,475
God all bloody mighty!
The <i>entente cordiale</i>?

794
00:58:49,760 --> 00:58:53,548
Cast the mote out of your eye
before you cast the bomb out of mine!

795
00:58:53,840 --> 00:58:56,229
He's a proper faggot.
Here, you'll like them.

796
00:58:56,480 --> 00:58:57,356
Thank you.

797
00:58:57,640 --> 00:58:59,676
Who's next?
Come on, girls.

798
00:58:59,960 --> 00:59:01,154
Speak up!

799
00:59:07,200 --> 00:59:11,478
l was wondering if you would also give
the girls some lessons in makeup.

800
00:59:13,080 --> 00:59:15,674
l think quite a few
of them would be...

801
00:59:16,320 --> 00:59:18,629
...very pretty if they knew
how to do it.

802
00:59:18,920 --> 00:59:20,512
Why, certainly.

803
00:59:26,200 --> 00:59:29,636
You are getting involved
with your children, aren't you?

804
00:59:29,920 --> 00:59:32,878
l'm just trying to help.
That's the job, isn't it?

805
00:59:33,240 --> 00:59:35,310
-You want some of this?
-No, thanks.

806
00:59:35,840 --> 00:59:37,512
ls that all you're having?

807
00:59:37,800 --> 00:59:39,358
You on a diet?

808
00:59:40,720 --> 00:59:42,995
l'll tell you, l'm a weak man.

809
00:59:43,440 --> 00:59:45,078
At the moment, a little skint.

810
00:59:45,360 --> 00:59:48,079
When l eat, do l love to eat!

811
00:59:48,360 --> 00:59:50,669
l love wine,
but l just can't have a glass.

812
00:59:50,960 --> 00:59:52,234
l want the whole bottle.

813
00:59:52,520 --> 00:59:55,432
So l avoid wine
and pastrami sandwiches...

814
00:59:55,720 --> 00:59:57,233
...and baked potatoes...

815
00:59:57,520 --> 01:00:00,717
...with butter and bacon...

816
01:00:00,960 --> 01:00:04,919
...and strawberry shortcake
and cheesecake.

817
01:00:08,400 --> 01:00:10,630
But l like to eat light for lunch.

818
01:00:14,520 --> 01:00:15,635
How's the Dare girl?

819
01:00:19,520 --> 01:00:21,033
No problems.

820
01:00:22,880 --> 01:00:25,713
-Are you gonna stay on here?
-Until l get sorted out.

821
01:00:26,360 --> 01:00:27,873
No luck with the jobs?

822
01:00:28,160 --> 01:00:29,832
But l'm plugging away.

823
01:00:31,800 --> 01:00:35,031
Remember a few weeks ago,
you thought you'd lost the battle?

824
01:00:36,440 --> 01:00:37,634
l thought you had too.

825
01:00:37,920 --> 01:00:40,559
There's a good angel
looking after me, somewhere.

826
01:00:44,640 --> 01:00:46,870
Come on.
Sort yourselves out.

827
01:00:48,640 --> 01:00:49,914
Come on, hurry up!

828
01:00:52,120 --> 01:00:53,872
All right? Go!

829
01:00:54,360 --> 01:00:56,510
Come on, Denham, hurry it up.

830
01:01:00,320 --> 01:01:03,437
Land on your toes.
Do it again. Next!

831
01:01:05,920 --> 01:01:06,670
Next!

832
01:01:10,760 --> 01:01:12,159
Buckley!

833
01:01:12,600 --> 01:01:13,350
Come on, boy.

834
01:01:13,640 --> 01:01:14,834
l'm not a boy.
l'm a man.

835
01:01:15,120 --> 01:01:16,872
l don't want to do it.
lt's too high.

836
01:01:17,160 --> 01:01:18,832
You're a fat boy.
Come on.

837
01:01:19,120 --> 01:01:20,792
l'm waiting.
Get that jelly off!

838
01:01:21,080 --> 01:01:23,150
Fats can't do it.
lt's too high for him.

839
01:01:23,440 --> 01:01:24,839
Of course, he can't do it!

840
01:01:27,480 --> 01:01:29,152
When l want your opinion,
l'll ask, boy.

841
01:01:29,440 --> 01:01:31,396
-l'm not a boy.
-Shut up!

842
01:01:34,320 --> 01:01:37,517
Buckley, do as you're told!

843
01:01:38,720 --> 01:01:39,914
Come on!

844
01:01:57,920 --> 01:02:00,115
-Move out of the way, boy.
-Shut up!

845
01:02:02,640 --> 01:02:03,390
ls he all right?

846
01:02:04,760 --> 01:02:05,556
l don't know.

847
01:02:12,080 --> 01:02:13,195
You bloody bastard!

848
01:02:13,480 --> 01:02:14,674
Put that down!

849
01:02:14,960 --> 01:02:17,838
You knew Fats couldn't do that.
You had it in for him.

850
01:02:18,320 --> 01:02:19,594
Potter, put that down!

851
01:02:24,880 --> 01:02:26,279
They're fighting in the gym!

852
01:02:28,720 --> 01:02:30,039
Come on, Potts!

853
01:02:35,000 --> 01:02:36,479
That was no accident!

854
01:02:39,800 --> 01:02:41,119
l'll take that.

855
01:02:45,880 --> 01:02:47,154
Go and help Buckley.

856
01:02:47,440 --> 01:02:48,555
Go on!

857
01:02:53,000 --> 01:02:55,753
Potts should have done the bastard
like he did Fats.

858
01:03:07,840 --> 01:03:08,636
You all right, boy?

859
01:03:08,920 --> 01:03:11,115
Yes, thank you.
Me stomach didn't half hurt.

860
01:03:11,400 --> 01:03:14,312
Jackson, lngram?
Help him up to Mrs. Evans.

861
01:03:19,400 --> 01:03:20,674
All right.

862
01:03:21,480 --> 01:03:22,833
What happened?

863
01:03:37,840 --> 01:03:39,193
Buckley's all right.

864
01:03:40,120 --> 01:03:42,395
More frightened than anything else.

865
01:03:44,880 --> 01:03:46,916
Why'd you make him do that jump?

866
01:03:47,840 --> 01:03:50,354
He just stood there
and refused to obey.

867
01:03:50,640 --> 01:03:54,076
When he jumped, he sent the buck flying
and l couldn't catch him.

868
01:03:56,480 --> 01:03:59,392
Thanks for helping me out.
That Potter went berserk.

869
01:04:04,200 --> 01:04:07,317
l understand that Buckley is
a pet whipping boy of yours.

870
01:04:07,600 --> 01:04:08,669
ls that right?

871
01:04:10,680 --> 01:04:13,353
l'd better report it.
There'll be the devil to pay.

872
01:04:43,200 --> 01:04:46,590
Potter, l can't think of anything
that excuses your behaviour.

873
01:04:47,760 --> 01:04:49,398
But it was him!
He made Fats do it.

874
01:04:49,680 --> 01:04:53,150
Fats said he couldn't do it.
The bully always had it in for him.

875
01:04:53,480 --> 01:04:55,869
l am not concerned with
Mr. Bell's behaviour, but yours.

876
01:04:56,160 --> 01:04:58,469
What if a gun or knife
had been handy?

877
01:04:59,120 --> 01:05:00,917
Potter was narked.
We was all narked.

878
01:05:01,200 --> 01:05:03,156
That bleeder was wrong
and you know it.

879
01:05:03,440 --> 01:05:05,874
You're missing the point.
You all are.

880
01:05:06,160 --> 01:05:08,230
Soon you will be out in the world.

881
01:05:08,520 --> 01:05:10,829
Will you use a weapon every time
someone angers you?

882
01:05:11,240 --> 01:05:13,800
You're supposed to
be learning self-discipline.

883
01:05:15,080 --> 01:05:17,435
You owe Mr. Bell an apology.

884
01:05:20,360 --> 01:05:23,557
Why?
Just because Bell is a teacher?

885
01:05:23,840 --> 01:05:25,751
You better answer that, Potter.

886
01:05:26,040 --> 01:05:28,190
Do you think you behaved
like an adult?

887
01:05:39,960 --> 01:05:41,837
How about Bell
apologizing to Buckley?

888
01:05:43,120 --> 01:05:46,192
My business is with you,
not Mr. Bell.

889
01:05:46,480 --> 01:05:49,472
lt's easy for you to talk.
No one pushes you around.

890
01:05:53,400 --> 01:05:54,913
Are you a man or a hoodlum?

891
01:05:59,160 --> 01:06:00,673
Do it, Potts!

892
01:06:02,280 --> 01:06:04,475
Or Bell will call the law
if you don't.

893
01:06:05,280 --> 01:06:08,113
You've got to have recommends
for a job in a couple weeks.

894
01:06:08,400 --> 01:06:09,549
He's got to sign one.

895
01:06:10,800 --> 01:06:13,268
This has nothing
to do with what l sign.

896
01:06:13,840 --> 01:06:15,512
You can't trust a teacher.

897
01:06:15,800 --> 01:06:18,360
We're only safe together.
Against them.

898
01:06:18,640 --> 01:06:20,596
But Sir is different.
lf he says Potts--

899
01:06:20,880 --> 01:06:23,348
That he is, and he's wrong now.

900
01:06:24,280 --> 01:06:27,238
You all know Bell's been after
old Fats for years.

901
01:06:31,840 --> 01:06:33,273
Go on, Potts.

902
01:06:43,000 --> 01:06:45,594
lf you apologize
because you're afraid...

903
01:06:45,880 --> 01:06:48,792
...then you're a child, not a man.

904
01:06:57,720 --> 01:07:00,439
When l leave,
l'll have me own barrow.

905
01:07:00,720 --> 01:07:04,872
So you can't touch me,
letters or no letters.

906
01:07:24,760 --> 01:07:26,273
l'm sorry l'm late, Sir.

907
01:07:28,840 --> 01:07:30,239
But it's me mum.

908
01:07:32,200 --> 01:07:33,758
She's dead.

909
01:07:35,440 --> 01:07:37,715
l've been helping me dad
with her things.

910
01:07:42,240 --> 01:07:45,949
-l didn't know where to go, Sir.
-That's all right.

911
01:07:47,040 --> 01:07:49,474
lngram, take over the class.

912
01:08:10,600 --> 01:08:13,353
l understand that
the passing-out class holds...

913
01:08:13,640 --> 01:08:16,791
...some kind of a celebration
at the end of term.

914
01:08:17,080 --> 01:08:18,399
What happens?

915
01:08:24,160 --> 01:08:25,354
We dance...

916
01:08:25,640 --> 01:08:26,914
...Sir.

917
01:08:30,440 --> 01:08:32,351
Did you apologize because of Denham?

918
01:08:37,040 --> 01:08:39,110
One should fight
for what one believes...

919
01:08:40,080 --> 01:08:42,674
...provided one is absolutely sure...

920
01:08:42,960 --> 01:08:45,394
...one is absolutely right.

921
01:08:46,960 --> 01:08:48,234
Pass these out.

922
01:08:59,040 --> 01:09:00,951
You have to fill those out...

923
01:09:01,840 --> 01:09:04,798
...for national health insurance
and so on.

924
01:09:32,040 --> 01:09:33,837
What are you doing, Jackson?

925
01:09:34,600 --> 01:09:36,830
lt's for Seales.
For flowers and a wreath.

926
01:09:38,600 --> 01:09:40,477
That's wonderful of you.

927
01:09:40,920 --> 01:09:43,514
May l be permitted
to contribute something?

928
01:09:43,800 --> 01:09:45,791
No, thank you, Mr. Thackeray.

929
01:09:48,000 --> 01:09:50,070
Here, Pam, you buy the wreath.

930
01:09:50,640 --> 01:09:51,789
The name's Dare.

931
01:09:52,080 --> 01:09:53,069
Miss Dare.

932
01:09:53,360 --> 01:09:54,873
Well, you buy the wreath.

933
01:09:55,440 --> 01:09:57,635
Send it around when the time's right.

934
01:09:59,040 --> 01:10:01,634
Send it?
Aren't you going to take it?

935
01:10:06,720 --> 01:10:08,950
You don't think
girls could take it, do you?

936
01:10:09,400 --> 01:10:11,311
Well, why not?

937
01:10:25,960 --> 01:10:28,315
lt's what people would say, Sir.

938
01:10:29,080 --> 01:10:30,877
What the family would say...

939
01:10:31,640 --> 01:10:35,030
...if they saw us going
into a coloured person's home.

940
01:10:35,960 --> 01:10:37,791
We've got nothing against you, Sir.

941
01:10:38,080 --> 01:10:39,195
Honest.

942
01:10:40,040 --> 01:10:41,837
But if one of us was to....

943
01:10:42,120 --> 01:10:44,315
You can't imagine the things be said.

944
01:11:09,960 --> 01:11:13,635
Thank you, Miss Pegg,
for making it clear.

945
01:11:16,920 --> 01:11:19,957
Does that apply to the men also?

946
01:11:20,760 --> 01:11:22,876
You're dead right it does.

947
01:11:31,720 --> 01:11:32,789
l'll take the flowers.

948
01:11:37,040 --> 01:11:38,553
Why should you do that?

949
01:11:38,840 --> 01:11:40,956
Wouldn't that make you
subject to gossip?

950
01:11:41,600 --> 01:11:45,639
Gossip don't worry me.
l've known Seales since kindergarten.

951
01:11:46,280 --> 01:11:48,191
l'll take the flowers.

952
01:11:48,920 --> 01:11:51,195
l wouldn't if l were you.

953
01:12:15,160 --> 01:12:16,752
l've been looking for you.

954
01:12:17,040 --> 01:12:19,508
There's a lady to see you.
Mrs. Dare.

955
01:12:21,160 --> 01:12:25,278
And by the way, l've canceled
all outings for your class.

956
01:12:26,440 --> 01:12:27,555
Why?

957
01:12:27,880 --> 01:12:29,552
The adult approach hasn't worked.

958
01:12:30,480 --> 01:12:32,357
lt'd have been better
to let things be.

959
01:12:32,640 --> 01:12:35,996
You'd better take your boys in for P.T.
until l get a replacement.

960
01:12:49,280 --> 01:12:52,670
l'm sorry to disturb you, Sir.
lt's about Pam.

961
01:12:52,960 --> 01:12:53,915
l'm Mrs. Dare.

962
01:12:54,200 --> 01:12:57,158
What can l do for you?
Would you have a seat?

963
01:12:57,440 --> 01:13:00,830
Would you talk to her, Sir?
l'm sure she'd listen to you.

964
01:13:01,120 --> 01:13:03,236
-She's always talking about you.
-What's the problem?

965
01:13:06,640 --> 01:13:09,154
She always stays out
late at night, Sir.

966
01:13:09,440 --> 01:13:11,829
Often she doesn't get home
till past 1 1 .

967
01:13:12,400 --> 01:13:14,516
She never says where she's been.

968
01:13:14,800 --> 01:13:17,360
She's a big girl.
l'm worried about her.

969
01:13:18,160 --> 01:13:19,275
She won't listen to me.

970
01:13:21,080 --> 01:13:22,798
l'm just a teacher, Mrs. Dare.

971
01:13:23,080 --> 01:13:24,513
l know she'd listen to you.

972
01:13:24,800 --> 01:13:28,031
lt's always ''Sir said this''
or ''Sir said that.''

973
01:13:29,080 --> 01:13:33,437
See, she won't listen to me.
She just won't.

974
01:13:34,040 --> 01:13:35,712
Why doesn't her father
talk with her?

975
01:13:38,120 --> 01:13:39,872
We're divorced.

976
01:13:40,160 --> 01:13:42,799
He's up north somewhere.
He doesn't--

977
01:13:45,480 --> 01:13:47,914
lt's not wrong to--

978
01:13:49,440 --> 01:13:52,716
When your marriage breaks up,
life doesn't end, does it?

979
01:13:53,680 --> 01:13:56,831
Please talk to her, Sir.
l'm frightened for her.

980
01:13:57,120 --> 01:14:00,476
You never know what sort
of trouble she can get into.

981
01:14:02,080 --> 01:14:03,149
Please?

982
01:14:06,400 --> 01:14:08,197
All right, l will.

983
01:14:09,080 --> 01:14:10,274
Thank you.

984
01:15:07,080 --> 01:15:08,229
Morning, Sir.

985
01:15:09,000 --> 01:15:09,796
Hello, luv.

986
01:15:10,080 --> 01:15:12,594
-Morning.
-How are you? How's the kids?

987
01:15:12,960 --> 01:15:13,756
Hello, Guv!

988
01:15:16,640 --> 01:15:18,710
Hello, Sir.
lt's a lovely day, isn't it?

989
01:15:19,000 --> 01:15:21,230
Your kid ain't top of the class.

990
01:15:41,880 --> 01:15:44,314
My, you look as if
you've won the pools.

991
01:15:44,800 --> 01:15:45,630
Better!

992
01:15:45,920 --> 01:15:48,718
l got me a job.
A real one for when school ends.

993
01:15:49,000 --> 01:15:51,514
Assistant engineer
in a factory in the Midlands.

994
01:15:51,800 --> 01:15:54,075
They even sent me the fare!

995
01:15:54,360 --> 01:15:55,509
That's marvelous.

996
01:15:55,800 --> 01:15:58,473
lt's not that good,
but it's a start after so long.

997
01:15:59,840 --> 01:16:01,637
Do you think
she'll take the flowers?

998
01:16:02,040 --> 01:16:03,268
l don't know.

999
01:16:06,280 --> 01:16:08,032
Go in. Sir wants you.

1000
01:16:22,240 --> 01:16:24,708
Sit down.
l'd like to talk to you.

1001
01:16:25,200 --> 01:16:26,997
Has my mum been in?

1002
01:16:30,840 --> 01:16:33,752
The funeral's Saturday, 1 0:30.

1003
01:16:37,200 --> 01:16:38,633
About my mum, Sir?

1004
01:16:38,920 --> 01:16:41,639
She's very worried about you,
Miss Dare.

1005
01:16:42,520 --> 01:16:44,317
Couldn't you call me Pamela?

1006
01:16:46,640 --> 01:16:48,710
l think not, for the moment.

1007
01:16:49,000 --> 01:16:52,072
She says that
you've been staying out late.

1008
01:16:52,360 --> 01:16:56,319
l've just been to Gran's.
Just around the corner, not far.

1009
01:16:57,280 --> 01:16:59,111
Why haven't you told your mother?

1010
01:16:59,400 --> 01:17:00,913
She doesn't care about me.

1011
01:17:01,200 --> 01:17:03,156
You know that's not true.

1012
01:17:06,760 --> 01:17:08,034
You're not in trouble, are you?

1013
01:17:10,640 --> 01:17:12,995
Nowadays that's only for fools,
isn't it?

1014
01:17:13,960 --> 01:17:16,520
We're the luckiest kids,
the luckiest generation...

1015
01:17:16,800 --> 01:17:19,075
...that's ever been, aren't we?

1016
01:17:19,360 --> 01:17:23,319
We're the first to be really free
to enjoy life if we want...

1017
01:17:23,600 --> 01:17:24,828
...without fear.

1018
01:17:26,160 --> 01:17:27,434
What is the trouble?

1019
01:17:28,880 --> 01:17:30,950
lf you don't want to talk,
say the word.

1020
01:17:32,080 --> 01:17:33,559
lt doesn't bother me.

1021
01:17:34,360 --> 01:17:37,193
lt was all right
up till about a year ago.

1022
01:17:37,680 --> 01:17:40,353
Of course, l miss Daddy.
He was wonderful.

1023
01:17:40,960 --> 01:17:43,030
But it's just one of those things.

1024
01:17:44,360 --> 01:17:47,432
Mum works up in a dress shop
on the West End.

1025
01:17:47,840 --> 01:17:49,432
And we got on fine.

1026
01:17:51,240 --> 01:17:53,879
Then men friends started
calling on her.

1027
01:17:54,960 --> 01:17:57,076
You know what neighbours are like.

1028
01:17:59,120 --> 01:18:01,714
That's all.
There's nothing else to tell.

1029
01:18:04,120 --> 01:18:07,157
She doesn't like me.
l'm in the way.

1030
01:18:07,880 --> 01:18:09,996
She's young and pretty, isn't she?

1031
01:18:10,600 --> 01:18:12,750
l'll be glad to leave school
and be on my own.

1032
01:18:14,640 --> 01:18:16,631
Obviously your mother loves you.

1033
01:18:16,920 --> 01:18:19,070
And you owe her much more
than any teacher.

1034
01:18:19,360 --> 01:18:21,669
l think you're wrong about her.

1035
01:18:21,960 --> 01:18:26,192
Did she tell you that l found her
with one of her friends?

1036
01:18:26,480 --> 01:18:28,596
At home? At my home?

1037
01:18:29,240 --> 01:18:31,390
No, l bet she didn't,
but she was!

1038
01:18:32,760 --> 01:18:36,514
l can't solve your problems for you.
But staying out late won't help.

1039
01:18:36,800 --> 01:18:39,075
lt helps me.
l can't stand the sight of her!

1040
01:18:39,360 --> 01:18:41,635
And if you were me,
you'd feel the same.

1041
01:18:41,920 --> 01:18:45,117
l'm in no position to judge.
l know people make mistakes.

1042
01:18:45,400 --> 01:18:46,674
You're saying it's my fault?

1043
01:18:46,960 --> 01:18:49,952
Forgiveness is the gift of God.
People make mistakes.

1044
01:18:50,240 --> 01:18:51,878
lt's up to you to make peace.

1045
01:18:52,520 --> 01:18:55,592
-Why should l? l haven't done anything.
-Grow up.

1046
01:18:55,920 --> 01:18:57,751
Give her another chance.

1047
01:18:58,160 --> 01:19:00,355
Why are you taking her side?

1048
01:19:00,920 --> 01:19:04,151
You're wrong not to give her a chance.
Everybody deserves that.

1049
01:19:06,720 --> 01:19:10,474
l thought you'd understand.
l thought l could trust you.

1050
01:19:10,760 --> 01:19:14,469
But you're just as Denham said.
l'm not taking the bloody flowers!

1051
01:20:05,280 --> 01:20:06,508
All right.

1052
01:20:08,800 --> 01:20:10,756
Let's line up here
in the centre.

1053
01:20:11,120 --> 01:20:13,111
Could we box first today, please?

1054
01:20:16,440 --> 01:20:17,190
Why?

1055
01:20:17,520 --> 01:20:18,919
lt would make a change.

1056
01:20:20,840 --> 01:20:23,149
Just sort yourselves in pairs now.

1057
01:20:24,200 --> 01:20:27,510
Do you mind having a go with me?
Sapiano's hurt his wrist.

1058
01:20:27,800 --> 01:20:29,313
That's right. l sprained it.

1059
01:20:33,680 --> 01:20:38,276
l think you ought to wait and have a go
at Potter or one of the others.

1060
01:20:38,560 --> 01:20:40,232
He'll be done in, Sir.

1061
01:20:42,160 --> 01:20:44,720
l don't mind having
a punch out with you.

1062
01:20:47,640 --> 01:20:50,313
l think you'd better
forget that for today.

1063
01:20:51,000 --> 01:20:52,353
Let's go!

1064
01:21:10,560 --> 01:21:11,356
Let's go.

1065
01:22:20,760 --> 01:22:22,113
Stay where you are!

1066
01:22:25,880 --> 01:22:27,313
Put your head down.

1067
01:22:30,480 --> 01:22:32,755
Collect the gloves and put them back.

1068
01:22:33,200 --> 01:22:35,634
The rest of you,
line up for vaulting.

1069
01:22:38,600 --> 01:22:39,953
Put your head down.

1070
01:22:43,640 --> 01:22:44,868
You all right?

1071
01:22:46,520 --> 01:22:48,988
-Come over here for a minute.
-l'm all right.

1072
01:22:55,160 --> 01:22:56,991
l think l'll go wash up.

1073
01:23:06,960 --> 01:23:08,188
You all right, mate?

1074
01:23:08,480 --> 01:23:09,515
Are you sure?

1075
01:23:20,720 --> 01:23:22,597
Can l ask you something?

1076
01:23:22,880 --> 01:23:25,440
-How many times did you hit me?
-Once.

1077
01:23:26,080 --> 01:23:28,355
l'm sorry,
l didn't mean to hurt you.

1078
01:23:28,640 --> 01:23:29,868
l lost my temper.

1079
01:23:30,280 --> 01:23:31,679
l was meaning to hurt you.

1080
01:23:31,960 --> 01:23:34,474
You did.
You're pretty good.

1081
01:23:34,760 --> 01:23:36,398
Why didn't you hit me again?

1082
01:23:37,080 --> 01:23:38,991
Why didn't you fight?
You had me easy.

1083
01:23:39,280 --> 01:23:41,316
l've been after you
since you got here.

1084
01:23:41,600 --> 01:23:43,477
Are you afraid or something?

1085
01:23:45,800 --> 01:23:48,394
Hitting you wouldn't solve much,
would it?

1086
01:23:48,680 --> 01:23:51,513
lt's the truth.
l don't understand you at all.

1087
01:23:52,640 --> 01:23:53,709
What's a barrow?

1088
01:23:54,000 --> 01:23:58,232
A barrow? With fruit on it.
A barrow!

1089
01:23:58,520 --> 01:24:00,238
You was wrong about Potts.

1090
01:24:00,600 --> 01:24:03,353
Yes, from his point of view,
at his age, l was.

1091
01:24:03,640 --> 01:24:06,438
-The girls was right about the gossip.
-From their point of view.

1092
01:24:06,720 --> 01:24:08,278
What other point is there?

1093
01:24:08,560 --> 01:24:10,994
You have to figure that out
for yourself.

1094
01:24:18,800 --> 01:24:21,712
Would you like a job teaching
the youngsters how to box?

1095
01:24:23,440 --> 01:24:27,479
l'll speak with Mr. Florian.
There will be some money for you.

1096
01:24:28,280 --> 01:24:29,952
Me? A bleeding teacher?

1097
01:24:30,240 --> 01:24:33,437
lt's important the youngsters
know how to defend themselves.

1098
01:24:34,520 --> 01:24:35,794
Why are you doing this?

1099
01:24:36,080 --> 01:24:38,913
Good luck with your barrow.

1100
01:25:02,520 --> 01:25:05,671
What's the matter?
You going to a bleeding wedding?

1101
01:25:07,920 --> 01:25:10,115
You don't half pong, Potts!

1102
01:25:11,080 --> 01:25:13,594
-What's up with you, Fats?
-Nothing, Bert.

1103
01:25:15,120 --> 01:25:17,429
Another week and
we'll be through here.

1104
01:25:18,400 --> 01:25:19,992
l ain't got a job yet.

1105
01:25:24,040 --> 01:25:26,076
You had the bleeder yesterday.
Lucky punch.

1106
01:25:28,480 --> 01:25:31,040
You got eyes in the back of your head.

1107
01:25:31,320 --> 01:25:34,073
He could have done me
with one hand behind his back.

1108
01:25:34,360 --> 01:25:38,114
And none of your bleeding here.
There's ladies present.

1109
01:25:42,040 --> 01:25:46,272
What Sir said about the truth,
it's kind of scary, isn't it?

1110
01:25:48,640 --> 01:25:49,993
Good morning.

1111
01:25:50,680 --> 01:25:54,593
About the party,
we've got a group and all.

1112
01:25:54,880 --> 01:25:57,440
And the girls is fixing the grub.
You coming?

1113
01:26:00,120 --> 01:26:00,916
You inviting me?

1114
01:26:02,160 --> 01:26:03,752
Yeah, you're invited.

1115
01:26:04,480 --> 01:26:05,833
Thank you.

1116
01:26:06,840 --> 01:26:08,432
lf l can, l certainly will.

1117
01:26:11,400 --> 01:26:14,756
What you said is right,
about a man making up his own mind.

1118
01:27:54,120 --> 01:27:55,712
My goodness!

1119
01:27:56,400 --> 01:27:58,391
You certainly look lovely.

1120
01:27:58,840 --> 01:27:59,829
Thank you.

1121
01:28:01,520 --> 01:28:03,954
Would you dance with me tonight?

1122
01:28:06,120 --> 01:28:07,314
Of course.

1123
01:28:07,600 --> 01:28:10,558
But nothing too fast.
l am getting too old for that.

1124
01:28:11,320 --> 01:28:12,992
We'll make it special.
Promise?

1125
01:28:13,320 --> 01:28:14,469
Promise.

1126
01:28:15,000 --> 01:28:16,069
Thank you.

1127
01:28:18,520 --> 01:28:21,318
Would you call me Pamela tonight?

1128
01:28:24,880 --> 01:28:25,630
Pamela.

1129
01:28:27,760 --> 01:28:28,954
Thank you.

1130
01:28:49,000 --> 01:28:51,468
Excuse me a minute, Bert.
lt's Pam.

1131
01:28:55,480 --> 01:28:57,198
-You look marvelous!
-You look great!

1132
01:28:57,480 --> 01:28:59,436
-Where's the other earring?
-lt's the thing.

1133
01:28:59,720 --> 01:29:02,188
-l wanna talk to the group. Come.
-Why?

1134
01:29:02,480 --> 01:29:03,879
Come on, l'll tell you.

1135
01:29:43,120 --> 01:29:44,394
Good evening.

1136
01:29:44,680 --> 01:29:46,113
l hear you're leaving.

1137
01:29:46,960 --> 01:29:48,154
lt's a pity.

1138
01:29:48,480 --> 01:29:50,391
l'm sorry about that.
You're damn good.

1139
01:29:50,680 --> 01:29:52,352
You've done wonders for this show.

1140
01:29:52,720 --> 01:29:54,836
Thank you very much.

1141
01:29:55,120 --> 01:29:58,556
Anybody can be an engineer,
but teaching this mob is....

1142
01:29:58,840 --> 01:30:00,876
l wish l had your gift.

1143
01:30:01,880 --> 01:30:03,916
Why so serious, Mark?

1144
01:30:04,200 --> 01:30:06,350
Good God, it's Weston!

1145
01:30:07,440 --> 01:30:09,158
Wrap up, Clinty.

1146
01:30:10,520 --> 01:30:11,748
Well, l'm damned!

1147
01:30:12,720 --> 01:30:15,188
He wasn't giving you
a hard time, was he?

1148
01:30:15,480 --> 01:30:16,959
On the contrary.

1149
01:30:47,760 --> 01:30:51,833
Will you wave your magic wand
and make me sweet 1 6 again?

1150
01:30:52,840 --> 01:30:53,955
Nothing to do with me.

1151
01:30:54,440 --> 01:30:57,159
A fine lad.
Your hand's in this, all right.

1152
01:31:10,680 --> 01:31:13,240
lf you must leave,
go to another school.

1153
01:31:14,000 --> 01:31:16,309
You can't waste your talent
on electronics.

1154
01:31:17,200 --> 01:31:19,919
Damn!
l swore l wouldn't interfere.

1155
01:31:41,760 --> 01:31:43,398
Would you like some more?

1156
01:31:44,400 --> 01:31:46,277
-Who made it?
-l did.

1157
01:31:46,640 --> 01:31:50,315
lt's salad North Quay,
one of Sir's special recipes.

1158
01:31:50,600 --> 01:31:52,909
lt's bloody marvelous, Barbara.

1159
01:31:53,200 --> 01:31:56,078
l mean, Miss Pegg.

1160
01:31:56,360 --> 01:31:58,920
Thank you, Mr. Weston,
l'm sure.

1161
01:31:59,400 --> 01:32:02,995
Actually, l don't like it.
l think it's terrible, don't you?

1162
01:32:14,200 --> 01:32:15,633
Blimey, l'm hot!

1163
01:32:16,040 --> 01:32:16,790
Thank you.

1164
01:32:17,080 --> 01:32:19,799
Excuse me, Sir.
l got the job l wanted.

1165
01:32:20,240 --> 01:32:20,990
That's wonderful.

1166
01:32:21,280 --> 01:32:23,430
-What is it?
-Pageboy at the Hilton.

1167
01:32:23,960 --> 01:32:26,315
He can't wait to get
all that Yankee money.

1168
01:32:26,600 --> 01:32:27,999
You're right there.

1169
01:32:28,280 --> 01:32:30,271
l don't want to be
a pageboy all me life.

1170
01:32:30,560 --> 01:32:32,630
Will you help me get
into night school?

1171
01:32:32,920 --> 01:32:34,069
l'd be glad to.

1172
01:32:34,360 --> 01:32:35,634
Ta, Sir.

1173
01:32:35,920 --> 01:32:37,956
You ain't half a dolly, Miss.

1174
01:32:39,320 --> 01:32:40,469
Ready, Pam.

1175
01:32:43,440 --> 01:32:44,714
Attention, everybody!

1176
01:32:45,720 --> 01:32:49,076
By special request,
it's a lady's choice.

1177
01:32:54,520 --> 01:32:55,396
Hold that, please.

1178
01:35:24,640 --> 01:35:27,359
Come on.
Everybody, come here.

1179
01:35:28,200 --> 01:35:29,474
Thank you.

1180
01:35:31,080 --> 01:35:34,072
Can l come and see you
sometimes, next term?

1181
01:35:34,360 --> 01:35:35,475
l won't be here.

1182
01:35:37,160 --> 01:35:38,673
Everybody's got to move on.

1183
01:35:39,280 --> 01:35:42,238
l'm glad l met you, though.
You've helped me a lot.

1184
01:35:43,440 --> 01:35:45,078
We were lucky to have you.

1185
01:35:45,360 --> 01:35:48,796
The whole world's waiting for you.
You're a smasher!

1186
01:35:49,080 --> 01:35:49,830
Thanks.

1187
01:35:56,640 --> 01:35:57,390
Bye.

1188
01:36:04,600 --> 01:36:07,194
Hold it! Listen, everybody.
l've got an announcement.

1189
01:36:07,480 --> 01:36:08,390
lt's about Sir.

1190
01:36:12,280 --> 01:36:15,078
We'd like to thank you
for everything you've done.

1191
01:36:16,120 --> 01:36:18,918
We'd like to give you
a present to remember us by.

1192
01:36:19,200 --> 01:36:20,952
-Come on, Babs.
-You mean, Miss Pegg.

1193
01:36:30,560 --> 01:36:32,630
<i>The time has come</i>

1194
01:36:34,760 --> 01:36:36,716
<i>For closing books</i>

1195
01:36:36,960 --> 01:36:39,997
<i>And long last looks must end</i>

1196
01:36:43,720 --> 01:36:46,359
<i>And as I leave</i>

1197
01:36:48,160 --> 01:36:51,596
<i>I know that I am leaving</i>

1198
01:36:51,880 --> 01:36:53,916
<i>My best friend</i>

1199
01:36:57,040 --> 01:36:59,952
<i>A friend who taught me</i>
<i>Right from wrong</i>

1200
01:37:00,280 --> 01:37:02,032
<i>And weak from strong</i>

1201
01:37:02,320 --> 01:37:04,436
<i>That's a lot to learn</i>

1202
01:37:06,040 --> 01:37:08,315
<i>What can I give you</i>

1203
01:37:08,560 --> 01:37:09,549
<i>In return</i>

1204
01:37:13,560 --> 01:37:15,312
<i>If you wanted the moon</i>

1205
01:37:15,560 --> 01:37:18,120
<i>I would try to make a start</i>

1206
01:37:18,400 --> 01:37:22,154
<i>But I would rather you let me</i>

1207
01:37:22,760 --> 01:37:24,716
<i>Give my heart</i>

1208
01:37:25,040 --> 01:37:28,350
<i>To Sir, with love</i>

1209
01:37:46,360 --> 01:37:48,430
Speech! Speech!

1210
01:38:23,440 --> 01:38:26,955
l think l'd better go
and put it away.

1211
01:38:56,840 --> 01:38:58,876
Evening, Guv.

1212
01:39:03,600 --> 01:39:04,828
Nice, isn't it?

1213
01:39:05,120 --> 01:39:07,759
l'm in your bleeding class
next term.

